# Festag Design System Governance

There is **one** design system for the entire platform. New pages, popups, settings, and features must use existing tokens and primitives — never invent local styles.

## Before implementing UI

Check that the work uses:

- Existing design tokens (`--festag-*`, `--fp-*`, `--al-*`, `--btn-prim*`)
- Shared spacing / radius / motion (sheet MS, Aeonik Regular for UI)
- Shared buttons (`ModalButton` / auth `.al-btn` / `--festag-btn-dark-*`)
- Shared forms (auth `.al-input` fill-step pattern — no focus rings)
- Shared modals (`components/Modal.tsx` + `festag-popup-styles.css`)
- Brand marks from `BrandMark` / official SVGs only

If it does not fit: **do not ship a one-off**. Extend the system first.

## Hard rules

- **Buttons:** one height / radius / hover / active / font (Aeonik Regular 400). Labels stay on one line (`white-space: nowrap`); shorten copy before wrapping.
- **Modals:** one structure — width, padding, stacked H1 (title + muted explanation max 2 lines), no small subtitle under H1, same backdrop dismiss hint.
- **Forms:** match login inputs; dark/light same rules (fill step, no stroke focus).
- **Textareas:** `resize: none`; auto-height only.
- **Brand logos:** current official SVGs, equal optical weight and size.
- **Auth footer:** present on every auth surface (login, register, recovery, verify, success).

## Don't

- Per-page button CSS that diverges from the system
- White special-case CTAs that ignore `--festag-btn-dark-*`
- Custom modal shells beside `Modal` / auth recovery sheet
- Kickers, page leads under `h1`, or middle-dot meta joins (see sibling rules)
